Description:
BlueSoft is an innovative software house belonging to the Orange Group. We were established in 2002 and currently, over 1000 engineers work with us! We have extensive experience in various industries. Our clients include companies from the financial, pharmaceutical, retail, banking, transport, and logistics sectors. From simple support to complex digital transformations – we effectively address technical and business needs by using almost 200 advanced technologies.

We're seeking an excellent Python Backend Developer to join our team, responsible for developing and maintaining high-performance backend services to support a React application. You will build and optimize RESTful APIs, backend logic, and ensure scalability, reliability, and performance. Collaborating with cross-functional teams, you'll integrate features, troubleshoot and resolve issues to ensure high availability, and contribute to architecture design while improving code quality through reviews.

What We're Looking For:


Excellent Python programming skills—this is a must for the role.
Experience with FastAPI is a plus, but not required—experience with other Python frameworks is also valuable.
Strong understanding of RESTful API design and backend architecture.
Solid knowledge of databases (SQL/NoSQL) and experience optimizing database queries.
Experience with cloud technologies, preferably AWS, as well as Docker and CI/CD pipelines.
Strong problem-solving skills, with the ability to debug and optimize complex systems.
A proactive and collaborative mindset, with the ability to work effectively in agile teams.
Excellent communication skills to explain technical concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.


We offer:


👨‍💻 Work in a team of interdisciplinary experts and technology enthusiasts, inspired by working in a flat hierarchy;
📈 Permanent full-time cooperation in an extraordinary company, which has been growing dynamically for 20 years;
🚀 Possibility of development in various IT projects realized for well-known and recognizable clients – leaders in their industries;
🥇 The ability to work with the latest technologies and the highest standards of development;
⌚️ Flexible working hours and a hybrid or fully remote working model (different arrangements apply in different teams, we do not impose any options);
☁ A number of initiatives supporting knowledge sharing and development, such as: internal training, thematic guilds, Cloud training and certification opportunities (technology partnerships in four clouds);
📣 Possibility to learn English or German online and English lessons for teams;
🏋️‍♂️ Multisport card and medical insurance;
⛵️ Sea adventures co-financed by company – we regularly sail in the Caribbean, Mediterranean or North Sea.
